  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "UuvdzO0kZW2f3/sxN7sdLOQnY6Q=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:44.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# Single-User Feeds Persist During Collaboration\n\nCollaboration does not rewrite or migrate the single-user feed layout. When Alice shares `doc-001` with Bob:\n\n## Alice still owns and maintains\n\n- `ph:v2:user:0xalice` \u2014 user manifest\n- `ph:v2:drive:drive-abc` \u2014 drive manifest\n- `ph:v2:doc:doc-001` \u2014 document manifest (her personal backup)\n\n## And adds on top\n\n- `ph:v2:collab:doc-001` \u2014 collaboration index\n- `ph:v2:ops:0xalice_signer:doc-001` \u2014 her op feed\n\n## Bob brings his own\n\n- `ph:v2:user:0xbob` \u2014 Bob's user manifest\n- `ph:v2:ops:0xbob_signer:doc-001` \u2014 Bob's op feed\n\n## Why\n\n- Single-user feeds serve as the user's personal recovery path \u2014 they can reconstruct their whole vault independently\n- Collaboration adds a real-time transport layer, it doesn't own the source of truth\n- If collaboration ends, the single-user feeds continue working unchanged\n",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:44.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:44.000Z"
    }
  },
